how did you quit smoking cigarettes that is the main thing is finding a new addiction once you have a gaping hole for a habit you used to do the only way to keep going is to replace it with something else the biggest reason why people can't quit is because you're just standing there waiting for the break here's some suggestions become an exercise health addict you'll be into repairing the damage done by the ciggerettes and getting more fit in the process you won't be so bored to have time to smoke or start teaching yourself an instrument or taking lessons you'll have your mind on something else anyway those might not be the best suggestions whatever you subtract from your life you need to add something of close to equal value in order to keep going Tobacco smoking Addiction Friends Cigarette Drug addiction Alexander Technique Cigarette Smoking Man M16 (rifle) Tobacco Procrastination Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Drug abuse Immortality Smoking pipe Health insurance Cannabis (drug) Arguments for and against drug prohibition The Smoking Room Methamphetamine Prostate cancer Causality Cocaine DNA repair Coffee and Cigarettes Alzheimer's disease Scientology beliefs and practices Babe Ruth Cigar Alcoholics Anonymous GunBound Liam Gallagher Ozone depletion Aquemini Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Philosophy of space and time Goodness and value theory Cryonics Hypnosis Ten Commandments Snus A Day in the Life Illegal drug trade GunZ The Duel Ozone hole Smoking fetishism Jane's Addiction Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Tobacco advertising The League of Gentlemen (comedy) Tom Waits Iggy Pop Red Hot Chili Peppers Lung cancer Ty Cobb Hikaru no Go Mojave people Divorce Vernon Schillinger Brian Jones (musician) Obsessive-compulsive disorder Drill bit Tai Chi Chuan Social rule Fire fighting Milton H. Erickson Humphrey Bogart USS Vestal (AR-4) Fecal incontinence Dragon Booster Storyteller System Breastfeeding Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Eric C